  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Despite such efficiencies and the skillful use of language by AI models and agents, it is important to recognize that agents lack intrinsic emotions, moral reasoning ability (Olson, 2024), human-like curiosity, and ability to reflect (Kissinger et al., 2022).",
    "Benefits of the use of LLMs on medical knowledge (Singhal et al., 2023), in medicine (Busnatu et al., 2022 (Busnatu et al.,, 2022;; Clusmann et al., 2023; Guevara et al., 2024; Omiye et al., 2024; Pan et al., 2024; Thirunavukarasu et al., 2023), and on Electronic Health Record (EHR) (Smolyak et al., 2024; Yang et al., 2022) are aplenty.",
    "Also, use of AI/LLMs in SLP have begun to appear in Australia (Adikari et al., 2024; Girardi et al., 2023; Scarinci et al., 2024), Canada and France (Azevedo et al., 2024), India (Aggarwal et al., 2025; Bhardwaj et al., 2024; Deka et al., 2025), Türkiye (Birol et al., 2025), the USA (Benway & Preston, 2024; Dangol et al., 2024; Kim et al., 2025; Li & Wu, 2024; Pierce, 2024; Suthar, Yousefi Zowj, et al., 2022 Yu et al., 2024) and, in Latin America (Gallano et al., 2025).",
    "These efforts suggest the widening deployment of AI in SLP.",
    "The domains of service delivery in SLP include collaboration, counseling, prevention, screening, assessment, treatment, and use of technology and service to the population."
  ],
